      "id": "bf3859e2-1356-4e2f-976a-4f1f27b9109e",
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The Du'a (supplication) that Prophet Muhammad (peace be upon him) recited for his grandsons, Al-Hassan and Al-Hussein, is as follows:\n\nArabic Transliteration:\n> \"u‛eedhukumaa bi kalimaat-illaahi-taammati min kulli shayṭaanin, wa haammatin, wa min kulli ‛aynin laammah.\"\n\nTranslation:\n> \"I seek protection for you in the perfect words of Allah from every devil, and every beast, and from every evil eye.\" (Al-Bukhari 4/119)【36†(About Islam)】.\n\nThis Du'a represents a prayer for protection, invoking Allah's perfect words to shield the Prophet's grandsons from all kinds of harm, including evil forces and malicious intent.",
      "created_at": "2023-10-08T20:38:43.141592",
